<br>
They are not used for soloing, they are used for charming, which often happens to be charm soloing.  Arcane Rune, ER, TD3, and uproar were all placed in game to help assist in the chanters upgraded ability in POP to charm, if you dont choose to recognize that thats your decision.  I KNOW VI didnt give us 3500HP in componentless runes because if we tash too early we get aggro.  Since chanters have been tashing for years now without any runes to help us why would now be any different?  Our 1 new tash spell gives no more aggro then our level 50's one. If this were the case they would of given shamans 3500HP in runes too for slow aggro.  <br>
<br>
Many spells and abilities in POP for chanters are geared  towards improving the chanters ability to charm and maintain a charmed pet.  Heres the new POP spells and abilities added to our lineup.  7 new abilities and spells that help us charm effectively.  <br>
<br>
Word of morell - 6 second AOE stun up to level 65 mobs - this is used to temporarily stop both a pet once it breaks charm and the mob it was  attacking long enough to recharm the pet once again.  This spell has no other benefit then that and it causes huge aggro on yourself<br>
Arcane Rune - 1500 HP componentless shield<br>
Uproar - 425HP Short term shield<br>
Eldritch Rune - Insta cast componentless 1500HP shield<br>
Command of Druzzil - High level charm<br>
Beckon - Mid-high level charm<br>
Total Domination - Reduces chance for charm to break<br>
<br>
Do you think VI gave us all this because we get tash aggro?  They want us to charm..plain and simple.  They improved and intended to improve the chanters ability to charm from how it was in the past with the release of POP.  Now that chanters are using charm more because yes its more feasible to do so now then it was in the past.<br>
<br>
If Verant nerfs charm itself and makes it an almost completely useless tool to chanters they then make all these abilites and spells useless as well.  I dont need 3500HP in runes on me when I tash, I just wait 5 seconds for the MA to get aggro and then tash.  When I dont have a pet thats when I sit down and pick my nose and turn the TV on.  Why?  Because I havent been blessed with 4600+ nukes or 2000HP dots, or a permanent pet thats worth using mana to even summon it.  My nukes and dots are not worth the mana cost to use and I need to use an additional 15 ability points or so to get any kind of control over my permanent summonable pet of gayness.  <br>
<br>
The major issues with a chanter and a level 60+ pet are DPS and exp gained soloing.  One way mentioned to solving this problem was to reduce exp gained with a charmed pet to half.  DC pets take hald if they outdamge you, why not make charmed pets the same?  Ill tell you why...its exploitable. <br>
<br>
Scenario..  I am in POV and have a golem for a pet, and its attacking a golem.  When the golem I am attaking reaches the point of nearly dead, I root it, dispell my pet, root my pet, then nuke to death the mob the pet was attacking...now I get full experience because I dont have a pet and all that damage it did doesnt matter cause now its an NPC again.  Then I nuke my pet to death and get full experience for that too. <br>
<br>
So how do we allow a chanter to keep the charm lineup without making it a useless ability and ruining half the tools we received with POP to make it effective while not getting insane experience soloing and at the same time lowering a pets DPS.  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
