1) The mob gets stuck in a wall or other technical problems.<br>
2) Your charmed pet gets killed by the mob you are fighting.<br>
3) An NPC gets the final hit on the mob.<br>
<br>
The 3rd way is probably the most uncommon and what you witnessed.  When 2 uncharmed NPCs are attacking eachother, it doesn't matter how much damage they do.  If I get killshot, I get the exp.  If they get the killshot, the corpse poofs.<br>
<br>
I witnessed this a lot in Paludal with my Beastlord.  I'd attack a beetle, and when it got low on health it would run towards the SH zone.  Occassionally a guard would path near and attack the mob I was killing.  I had to nuke it to ensure I could get the killshot over the guard so I would get exp.  <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.aol.com/nodnarbjh/csig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
