<br>
In particular:<br>
<br>
1) Do not suggest that other posters have hidden agendas, or seek to harm others.<br>
2) Do not suggest that other posters lack intelligence, integrity, or are in serious need of a clue.<br>
<br>
Really, there is nothing you need to say that you cannot take a few extra seconds and rephrase it in a less negative way.<br>
<br>
If you were an enchanter, you'd probably feel pretty edgy, since the odds favor <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Verant</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> over-nerfing in response to player outcries.  If charmed is nerfed hard enough, enchanters will lose their only real outlet for kicking booty.<br>
<br>
If you were a mage, you might well feel threaten when one of the three best support classes appears to be destined to be the best damage dealing class as well, and also fearful that whatever <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Verant</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> does will over-nerf and hurt you as well.  Also, some mages hurt from the loss of non-charm soloing in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>PoP</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
There is enough anxiety without us attacking each other.<br>
<br>
As <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Hal 9000</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> once suggested: <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Relax, take a stress pill, and think things over.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
