<br>
tie charm duration to number of group members.  you know that can be checked because of the xp bonus for adding people to groups.  take whatever the duration of the charm is now, that becomes the 6-member-group charm duration.  for every spot in the group NOT filled, the duration is reduced by 15% to the lower end of a solo chanter getting 25% max duration.  rules for break-early and such still apply as stated, this would be max duration only.<br>
<br>
this should be fairly easy to code in.  all the appropriate runes/AA's/gear used for charming are still good to have.  charm still does totally insane damage in groups.  charm-soloing is effectivly dead in one shot, without affecting enchanter's groupability in any way.<br>
<br>
AFTER something like that goes in, then they might want to consider charm in group settings for rebalancing.  but i really don't think it's that messed up in a group setting that it needs to be totally trashed there.  if they capped a charmed mob's damage per hit at 300 or so that would definately balance it, possibly not even that much of a change would be needed.<br>
<br>
------------<br>
the major issue, i believe, that upsets people on the charm issue is very simple.  if charm soloing is done with skill there is near zero risk (even if you died every 3rd pull you could still come out ahead) to the enchanter.  it's not that charm itself is overpowered, it's just this one facet of it's use.  call it jealousy or class envy, even some kind of anti-chanter conspiracy if it makes you feel better, but what it comes down to is that people love chanters in a group, they want them to be powerful there.  However, in PoP soloing is DEAD except for uses of charm, this ability is a slap in the face of the non-charm classes who must find groups to do anything at all at 65.<br>
