<br>
1)Add a 1% slow component to all the PoP charms(seems a developer at SoE had the same idea)<br>
<br>
2)Prevent mobs charmed with PoP charms from accepting items/weapons given to them.  Giving a mob two summoned weapons to make it dual wield is just as big a DPS boost as hasting it.<br>
<br>
3)Give PoP charms(non-bard, at least) a recast on the order of 30-45 seconds.  The vast majority of charms last longer than this, but when you get unlucky you'll have to mez/FD/root instead of just chain-charming the mob.<br>
<br>
<br>
I think this will fix most of the charm issues.  The log posted here of a charmed pet doing 1,000 DPS over the course of a fight was due in great part to the fact that it had Burnout V and two summoned weapons.  Enchanters, mages, necromancers, and druids will still be able to have pets that do an easy 200-400 DPS, but they won't be able to outdamage a full group anymore.<br>
<br>
